Carol Lloyd was left injured and covered in blood after rocks were thrown at her car near Johannesburg in the latest wave of anti-immigrant protests . 
  Six people have been killed in the violence which started in Durban and has spread to Johannesburg . 
  Police fired tear gas and rubber bullets to disperse 200 protesters who pelted vehicles and police with rocks . 
  Protests began two weeks ago and have spread to other parts of the country . 
 